    <entry>
      <title>Encrypt Command Line Tool</title>
      <link href="/2020/02/12/Encrypt-Command-Line-Tool/"/>
      <url>/2020/02/12/Encrypt-Command-Line-Tool/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://crates.io/crates/encrypt" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img src="https://img.shields.io/crates/v/encrypt.svg" alt="Version info"></a></p><p>Support md5 &amp; sha1 &amp; sha2 &amp; sha3 encryption for file and string.</p><p>Install:</p><pre><code>cargo install encrypt</code></pre><p>USAGE:</p><pre><code>encrypt &lt;SUBCOMMAND&gt;</code></pre><p>FLAGS:</p><pre><code>-h, --help       Prints help information-V, --version    Prints version information</code></pre><p>SUBCOMMANDS:</p><pre><code>help          Prints this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)keccak224     keccak256     keccak384     keccak512     md5           sha1          sha224        sha256        sha3-224      sha3-384      sha3-512      sha384        sha512        sha512T224    sha512T256    </code></pre><p>USAGE:</p><pre><code>encrypt func [OPTIONS] --input &lt;input&gt;</code></pre><p>FLAGS:</p><pre><code>-h, --help       Prints help information-V, --version    Prints version information</code></pre><p>OPTIONS:</p><pre><code>-i, --input &lt;input&gt;      Input string or file path-o, --output &lt;output&gt;    Output uppercase or lowercase,  o = (u or l) [default: l]-t, --t &lt;t&gt;              Input-type t = (str or file) [default: str]</code></pre>]]></content>
      
      
      <categories>
          
          <category> Rust </category>
          
      </categories>
      
      
        <tags>
            
            <tag> Rust </tag>
            
        </tags>
      
    </entry>
    
    
    
